//SELENCE.BAF
@5090 = ~Selence Hillstar:  Owed Money

It seems that my newest contact, a thief in Athkatla, knows something about who has been looking for me.  She has struck a deal with these people but won't tell me who just yet, and thinks she needs to test me first.  I'm not sure what its all about yet, but she says some Amnish noble owes her money.  I'm to retrieve the gold from his safe at this noble's home in the government district of Athkatla.~

//CBPROM06.BAF
@5091 = ~No More Shadows Over Soubar

After defeating Rolf Sureblade and his bandits in Lyrar's Hold, I returned triumphantly to Soubar.  It was a warm reception, and I was offered the honorable position as Mayor of Soubar.  I couldn't accept it, however, and must continue on with my career as an adventurer.  The folk here are too busy rebuilding their homes, farms, or other property destroyed in the raids, and deserve a leader that they can count on.~
@5092 = ~Chief Lieutenant Promotion

The mayor of Soubar has rewarded me with the promotion to Chief Lieutenant.  Imagine, me, a simple <PRO_GIRLBOY> from Candlekeep becoming the <PRO_SONDAUGHTER> of a dead god and even rising high in the ranks of a Chief Lieutenant!~
@5093 = ~Chief Lieutenant Promotion

Gaius, the Paladin of Soubar has rewarded me with the promotion to Chief Lieutenant, in the absence of an elected official.  Imagine, me, a simple <PRO_GIRLBOY> from Candlekeep becoming the <PRO_SONDAUGHTER> of a dead god and even rising high in the ranks of a Chief Lieutenant!~
@5094 = ~Assault on Lyrar's Hold

After the assault the bandits perpetrated against Soubar, I have been authorized to use whatever force is necessary to defeat the bandits, including my own attack on their stronghold.  I've discussed the options of such an attack with the Major, but many of his men were wounded or killed in the bandit raid and he cannot afford to send men to assist me.  I will have to do it alone.  He has shown me two ways into the Keep:  an overland route which would force me to seige the castle's bailey walls, or a network of tunnels running below ground from Soubar to the Hold.  I do not know which way I will take, but both will be dangerous in their own ways.  Major has wished me good luck in my mission, and I hope to return to Soubar soon.~

//CBPROM05.BAF
@5095 = ~No More Shadows Over Soubar

After defeating Rolf Sureblade and his bandits in Lyrar's Hold, I returned triumphantly to Soubar.  It was a warm reception, and I have taken over the honorable position as Mayor of Soubar.  I don't expect that there will be much to do, as many of the folk are too busy rebuilding thier homes, farms, or other property destroyed in the raids.  For now, I think I will settle down for a while.~

