//CBSBIN75.D
@50100 = ~Spy in Soubar!

Unconfirmed reports from the Mayor's office and the Major show that the bandits may be getting some information about Soubar, it's resources, defenses, and the like from an inside man.  I do not know who this could be, but I will root out the spy, if one does exist.  He will pay for his treachery.~
@50101 = ~Possible Spy Suspects

I've spoken with my old friend Winthrop about some of the happenings in Soubar which could hint at the fact that there is, or could be, a spy in Soubar.  A ranger who was visiting Winthrop's inn at the time overheard our conversation, and helped me to work out who could possibly be the spy.   We made a list of these suspects, and I will investigate each of them.
*Ranger in Winthrop's Inn
*Winthrop himself
*The Mayor of Soubar, Sirrus Melandor
*Someone who bought A. Miller's house
*Someone, or someones, in the Soubar Social Club
*The boy I rescued from the farm, Charlie
*Displaced farmers fighting in an old warehouse.~
@50120 = ~Spy in Soubar?

I believe that I may have solved the mystery of a spy in Soubar.  I think that it is Winthrop, the man I thought was my freind, but he pleads innocence.  I have jailed him below the Guard Barracks where he will have to await trial.~
@50121 = ~Spy In Soubar:

It seems that the Major's suspicions have proved true.  There was a spy in Soubar, and it turned out to be, of all people, my old friend Winthrop.  Rolf Sureblade rescued him and I was ambushed during the melee.~

//CB285FTX.D
@50122 = ~Spy In Soubar:

It seems that the Major's suspicions have proved true.  There was a spy in Soubar, and it turned out to be the fighters who used to be farmers in outlying farms near Soubar.  Rolf Sureblade rescued them and I was ambushed during the melee.~
@50123 = ~Spy in Soubar?

I believe that I may have solved the mystery of a spy in Soubar.  I think that it is the fighters who were displaced from their farms near Soubar, but they plead innocence.  I have jailed them below the Guard Barracks where they will have to await trial.~

//CB428MJ.D
@50103 = ~Promotion

Major has promoted me to the rank of Staff Sergeant for the work I've done in the Soubar Militia.  I expect that with this rank comes greater responsibility, but also greater rewards.~
@50105 = ~Soubar Militia Promotion!

Once again, the Major was quite pleased with my completion of the missions he ordered me to perform.  He has awarded me a promotion, that to rank of Captain.  I am pleased with this, because it means that I will no longer need to use Soubar issued equipment and can use my own weapons and armor.~

//CBCHRRAN.D
@50124 = ~Spy in Soubar?

I believe that I may have solved the mystery of a spy in Soubar.  I think that it is the Ranger who was staying at Winthrop's inn, but he pleads innocence.  I have jailed him below the Guard Barracks where he will have to await trial.~

//CBISSON2.D
@50125 = ~Spy In Soubar:

It seems that the Major's suspicions have proved true.  There was a spy in Soubar, and it turned out to be the man who I had originally met back in Trademeet, Ceeb Isson.  Rolf Sureblade rescued the man and I was ambushed during the melee.~

//CBSIRRUS.D
@50126 = ~Soubar Attacked!

Soubar was attacked by a small contingent of bandits earlier, and the death toll could not even be calculated.  I do not know how many Soubarians or guardsmen lost their lives to the bandits, but I am becoming increasingly upset that Major will not allow me to attack the keep known as Lyrar's Hold.  Something must be done for the town, and I feel that I am wasting my time by defending it.~
@50127 = ~Spy In Soubar:

It seems that the Major's suspicions have proved true.  There was a spy in Soubar, and it turned out to be, of all people, the Mayor of Soubar himself, Sirrus Melandor.  Rolf Sureblade rescued the Mayor and I was ambushed during the melee.~
@50106 = ~Arrived in Soubar

We've finally arrived in the town of Soubar.  I've met with the mayor of the town, a man by the name of Sirrus Melandor.  He seems to be quite concerned about his town and the consequences it would face if the bandits were able to take control of the community.  Melandor is reluctant to send me straight out to do battle with the bandits harrassing the communities in the Chionthar Valley, and I agree with him.  Violence is not always the answer, and we all feel that if violence can be avoided, it would be best.  He has asked me to join up with the Soubar Militia, hoping that I will be able to defend the town and at the same time earn the respect of the villagers.  This I will do, and indeed, I will strive to make a difference within Soubar and defend its populous with my life.~

//CBSOUMJ1.D
@50107 = ~Enlisted

I've met with the leader of the Soubar Militia, the Major.  I've enlisted as a private in the military, and was forced to turn over all my personal belongings to the militia.  I am told, however, that they will be kept safe and that once I am released from my duties or promoted to an enlisted officer, all my belongings will be returned.  But for now, I will remain a private in the Guard.~
@50108 = ~Road Patrol

The Major has given me my first mission as a Private.  I am to report to the sergeant on the northern edge of Soubar where I will begin a tour of guard duty.  I do not know if the bandits will attempt to break through into town, but with me on the watch, I will do all that I can to prevent the death of innocent villagers in Soubar.~
@50102 = ~Rescue Scouts

Major has given me another mission.  Along with a sergeant, we'll be heading up to an outlying farm north of Soubar.  He has reported that a scouting party was ordered into that area to observe the tactical movements of the bandits.  Unfortunately, they did not return from their own mission, and Major wants me to find out what has happened to them.~

//CBSOUMJ2.D
@50104 = ~Displaced Villagers

Major has assigned me a mission in which he wants me to police the town.  As the bandits have sacked the village of Triel, west of Soubar, many of the refugees who escaped that town have migrated to Soubar.  Major is afraid that they will cause problems for Soubarians or the businesses, and asked that I spend time at the Narwhal, a posh inn/tavern on the west side of Soubar.  ~
@50109 = ~Training Militia Men

Since the incident at the Narwhal, Major has ordered me to begin the training of the Triel prisoners in hopes that they will be able to assist Soubar against the bandits.  This I will have to do, but Major has hinted that he is pleased with my performance and will promote me once again if the men are trained properly.~

//CBSOUMJ3.D
@50111 = ~Messenger Boy

I thought that becoming a Captain would give me certain privileges in the Soubar militia, but apparently not.  Major has requested that I deliver two letters to the leaders of powerful organizations in Amn.  One letter needs to go to Prelate Wessalen, leader of the Order of the Most Radiant Heart.  The other will be brought to Trademeet and delivered to Lord Logan Coprith.~
@50128 = ~Assault on Soubar!

The bandits, in retribution for the trouble I have caused Rolf Sureblade, have made an all out assault on Soubar.  Many, many villagers, guard, and others have died or gone missing in the attack.  I was able to beat off the bandits, but some happened to escape.  For this outrage, I shall hunt each bandit which has caused this trouble to the ends of Faerûn if I have to.  I have told the Major what occured, and he has told me that his Chief Lieutenant was slain while fighting the bandits.  He wants me to take the position, and I would be pleased to take over that coveted post.~
@50110 = ~Captain of a Company

The Major has assigned me a company of Soubar guards.  He has asked that I order the men to do the tasks that I used to do, guarding and patrolling the town, and to use my own judgement in doing so.  Major told me that the company was assemble outside the guard barracks and awaited me there.~

//CHARLOTJ.D
@50113 = ~Ranger Status:  Charlotte

As a ranger, Charlotte seems to know quite a bit about the region near Soubar, especially the woodlands south of Soubar and west of Baldur's Gate.  It is indeed fortunate that she was helping us, as we had to cross the mighty River Chionthar.  The point where we crossed had some swift undercurrents and was indeed COLD!  Thankfully, Charlotte told us all what to do, and we were able to get from the southeast bank to the northwest bank with little trouble.
And Charlotte is becoming more and more like a ranger again.  Hopefully, she'll regain her status soon.~
@50114 = ~Ranger Status:  Charlotte

Charlotte the fallen ranger and I have returned for a quick check on the River Chionthar's headwaters.  Things look like they are just about back to normal there.  It is good, and we think that the belladonna poison dumped in the waterway was not in large quanities, so the impact on wildlife and communities downstream will be minimal.
And Charlotte is closer still to understanding how she has fallen from grace as a ranger, and has taken a step closer to regaining the respect of others as a true Ranger.~
@50208 = ~Ranger Status:  Charlotte

Charlotte has recovered her ranger status.  It is good to see her happy once again.~

//CHARLOT0.D
@50115 = ~River Chionthar Cleaned Again!

After encountering a fallen ranger and her pet lion, we found that the mighty Chionthar running down to Baldur's Gate had been poisoned by an unwitting ogre.  The ogre, Narulf by name, had been instructed by his boss to toss a number of bottles of belladona juice into the river.  The ranger had been attempting to help a number of wild beasts who became ill and rabid from the belladona.   It was indeed lucky that we came upon the ogre before the enviornment took to much damage and may have been unable to heal itself naturally.  As we did discover the acts of Narulf in time, the river will of course clean itself as it runs its course; no pun intended.  Perhaps we'll return to see how well nature is recovering in a few days.~

//CB232CLU.D
@50200 = ~Spy In Soubar:

It seems that the Major's suspicions have proved true.  There was a spy in Soubar, and it turned out to be the boy I rescued from a farm, Charlie.  Rolf Sureblade rescued the boy and I was ambushed during the melee.~
@50202 = ~Burning Farms

While fighting bandits at a farmstead north of Soubar, I found a young boy by the name of Charlie.  He was able to escape the bandits and avoided his own death by hiding within the apple orchard.  He has told me that he saw what happened to his family when the bandits attacked the farm, but did not happen to see any Soubar scouts in the area.  I do not know if they had actually passed through the farm, nor if they themselves had been ambushed and killed by the bandits.  I will return to Soubar and report this to the Major.~

//CBWILLMA.D
@50201 = ~Sir William's Man Troubles

It seems that Selence Hillstar caught one of Athkatla's more prominent nobles in a compromising situation.  I'm not sure how he will resolve it for himself, but as far as I am concerned, I've got the key to his safe and am now going to get his money for Selence as a bribe to keep her quiet about Sir William's bedroom affairs.~

//CBLDBUCK.D
@50203 = ~Lord Hammerhand Bucko's Mansion

I was successfully able to clear out Bucko's mansion from the werebeast's infestation.  I don't think that they will return, but I may visit him again just to be sure.~

//CBISSON1.D
//CBCUTDF2.D
@50204 = ~A Lesser Bhaalspawn?

Could it be true?  I met a sorcerer today at Vyatri's in Trademeet.  He seemed a bit off his nut, but knew about me.  He said that he also had the blood of Bhaal in his veins, but whether through birth or vile experiments like what Irenicus conducts, I do not know.  It matters not either way.  Ceeb Isson, the powerful and god-like Bhaalspawn sorcerer, told me that there were some folks looking for me.  He did not know if they wanted me for good or ill, but I have a feeling I will meet them, and find out.

Hopefully, I will also have the chance to test my mettle against Ceeb, for I suppose there can only be one by the time I am finished.~

//TOMASTOJ.D
@50205 = ~Rats Rats Rats

A professional in Athkatla had taken the afternoon off from his trade and must have unwittingly acquired a Pipe of the Sewer.  He had been playing it for quite some time, and drew hundreds of rats to the city.  I was able to persuade him to stop playing the pipe, and he retired back to his trade.  The rats have lost the attraction they had for this Piper, and eventually will find other areas to infest.~

//TOMASTO1.D
@50206 = ~Tomas hunts after a half-orc named Sureblade.  He has told us that Sureblade has killed someone close to him.~

//SELENCE.D
@50207 = ~Selence Finally Gave Me Something Useful

Selence Hillstar, the smuggler/fence in Athkatla, has finally told me what I need to know.  She gave me a key which will open a locked door in an inn someplace in the city.  She said it was a popular inn, and there's only two major inns here in Athkatla.  The Five Flagons, where I met her earlier, would be a good choice, but on the other hand, the Copper Coronet is another popular tavern.  It must be one of those.  From there, she said I would find something to lead me to those men that have been looking to meet with me.  I shall have to go to one of those taverns and see if I can find any clues.~

