@20375 = ~CHARLOTTE was raised upon the isolated island of Elves, Evermeet, Charlotte was trained in the classic areas of art, literature, religion, history, music, and drama.  Her studies, while enjoyable, were not something that Charlotte felt would be something that would make her a productive member of her culture.  She may have had the knowledge of other's great work- been able to identify the exact year a painting was originally painted and by whom, but she had not the skill or creative talent to produce her own original works.  It was then that Charlotte decided she needed something else.  Upon completing her studies as a young elf, Charlotte left the island and against her forefather's and family's wishes, traveled to to the mainland while most other Elves were leaving for Evermeet.  
	Charlotte roamed the woodlands for decades before realizing she was a ranger.  She was never formally trained in the art of being a ranger, it more or less was an epiphany to her.  She took her new found career seriously, and was quite talented.  Whether as an elf or a woman of nature, it matters not how she became talented at the ranger skills.
	Recently, Charlotte lost her faith for some reason that she is not very forthcoming about, and lost her status as a ranger.  However, she is a ranger at heart, and will regain the status of rangerhood eventually.~
