@20608 = ~This is a golden urn with a strange substance coating the rim and interior.  The substance is almost like a liquid ash, quite fine in texture as if something had been burnt at extremely high temperatures.~
@20609 = ~This is quite obviously a phylactery of a lich.  You have had enough experience to know that the only way to completely destroy a lich is by destroying its phylactery when it is near.  If the phylactery is not destroyed, a hurt lich will reform itself in less than twenty days.  Destroying the phylactery immediately kills the lich.~
