@20617 = ~Letter of Introduction~
@20618 = ~Child of Bhaal-

Forgive the manner in which we contact you.  We have been searching throughout Amn and along the Sword Coast for someone powerful enough, and with enough skills and influence to assist us in the region of our home villages.

Know then, that if you decide to help us, please do not fail to bring this letter of introduction, along with the sealed letter accompaning it, to the Umar Hills Inn.  Do not unseal the following letter, for if you do unseal it before meeting with us, our homes may be jeapordized with the words we have written.

Truly, we hope to meet with you soon, as what we have heard about your abilities, compassion, and doings have pleased us and given hope to our villages and hearts.

Respectfully,

GV & AK~
@20619 = ~Sealed Letter~
@20620 = ~Broken-Sealed Letter~
@20621 = ~This is the sealed letter which accompanied the letter of introduction you found in the Copper Coronet.

It has been sealed with a wax, and embossed with a crest which you do not recognize.

As you were instructed to bring the letter of introduction and this sealed letter to the Umar Hills Inn, it would probably be unwise of you to unseal it at this point.~
@20622 = ~This is the letter which had an impressed seal of a crest which you did not recognize over the edges of the parchment.  You were instructed not to unseal the letter prior to meeting with the contacts at the Umar Hills Inn.  Now that you have unsealed it, you can see that there are black and red runes written in a flowing script and block runes that you can read to the left.~
