@20636 = ~This letter is addressed to Prelate Wessalen, the leader of the  Order of the Most Radiant Heart in Athkatla.  You are to deliver it to him for the Major of Soubar.


My most noble Prelate-
I trust this missive finds you in good health and in the gayest of spirits.  I fear all is not well in Soubar, as we have been besieged by the most violent bandits to have attacked any innocent village since before the Fall of the Gods.  Please, Prelate, in Torm's good name, we beg your assistance.  Any of the Order who would help us combat this threat are more than welcome to come to Soubar.  We await your assistance and pray that Torm delivers help to us.

With Torm's Blessing-
(the signature is scribbled and you cannot make out the name)
Major of Soubar~
@20637 = ~Vanshir's Warblade~
@20638 = ~The warrior Vanshir travelled for a great time with an mercenary party, some of whom he did not trust as to their greed and selfish acts, yet he fought valiantly to keep them safe.  After a great battle, with the company weakened, a thief decided to make his life easy and lay claim to other's belongings.  He started witht he first and most powerful warrior, Vanshir.  The foul man stuck a poison dagger in his back and went to work on the rest of the party.  Vanshir survived and made his way to a nearby city to rest and heal, and three years later, without the aid of magic to get him home, he made his way to his estates.  It was here that he became obsessed with revenge and sold all that he owned, called in all of his favors, and alienated most of his friends.  He used this money to pay off a wizard to craft an enchanted blade that he would use to hunt down and kill thieves.

The Warblade is a +3 longsword that grants immunity to fear, +3 to AC, and +1 to saving throws.  It glows a sickly green and throbs.

STATISTICS:

