@20708 = ~Typically carried by travellers, scholars, and adventurers, this leather sack can be worn over one or both shoulders, or it can be carried by the reinforced leather handle above the flap.  It can be tied closed, preventing the contents from spilling out during travel.  The sack has numerous smaller pouches sewn along the outside to keep smaller items like writing quills, bottles of ink, or loaves of bread from making a mess of the inside compartment.  There are also leather thongs for safe storage during travel.

